1
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:36,745
Wait. Time out!

2
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:41,583
You can't leave.

3
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:43,418
Alex, I'm not lying to you.

4
00:00:43,501 --> 00:00:45,962
I'm telling the truth that Chiara
is no longer a Moraviano.

5
00:00:47,213 --> 00:00:50,216
There's a tactical squad positioned
right outside this room,

6
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:52,469
so you have nowhere to run.

7
00:00:58,349 --> 00:01:01,144
Who is La Morte Bianca? Is she even real?

8
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:03,104
Yes! Of course she is.

9
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:07,859
If we thought before that the Moravianos
were our only enemies,

10
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:09,277
we were very wrong.

11
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:10,987
There's something worse.

12
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:14,741
There's a bigger force that is about
to descend upon the entire Philippines.

13
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:28,064
Kare-kare.

14
00:04:13,127 --> 00:04:16,339
You probably think you can fool me
because you're La Fornarina, huh?

15
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:22,011
You Moravianos are all the same.

16
00:04:27,058 --> 00:04:28,685
I'm not fooling you.

17
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:40,238
Why don't you first prove to me

18
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:43,199
that the information
you're offering is valuable?

19
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:46,411
Then I'll decide whether it's truly worthy

20
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:49,247
of immunity from prosecution.

21
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:54,460
Not you being the one making demands.

22
00:04:58,172 --> 00:04:59,841
I know what you're doing.

23
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:08,558
So annoying.

24
00:05:09,559 --> 00:05:10,977
Can you talk to your girlfriend?

25
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:14,897
I can make suggestions,
but I could never dictate to her.

26
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:17,442
Because, you know, Agent Alex,
when it comes to our relationship,

27
00:05:17,525 --> 00:05:20,653
we value, you know,
mutual respect and independence.

28
00:05:20,737 --> 00:05:22,864
We don't have traditional gender roles

29
00:05:22,947 --> 00:05:25,908
because we view each other as equal.

30
00:05:26,659 --> 00:05:27,493
Right?

31
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:31,998
You need vital information, right?

32
00:05:32,081 --> 00:05:33,750
I can give you that.

33
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,376
But this is a game changer.

34
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,170
Just make sure you're ready.

35
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:42,633
You talk like it's such a game changer.

36
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:45,136
Wait, wait. This is not overhype, huh?

37
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:47,597
Think of it this way,
Agent Alex. In a TV drama,

38
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,349
the information Chiara has
is Book 2 material.

39
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:52,018
Yes, that's how intense it is.

40
00:05:52,101 --> 00:05:53,644
The kind that keeps you hooked.

41
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:56,689
So if I were you, give Chiara a chance.

42
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:58,357
Hear her out first.

43
00:06:08,326 --> 00:06:10,036
They said our salary's in!

44
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:13,790
Salary today,

45
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:16,167
just a memory tomorrow.

46
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:17,710
Well, that's life.

47
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:20,922
So before it all gets eaten up by bills,

48
00:06:21,005 --> 00:06:23,382
- let's have samgyupsal first.
- Samgyupsal it is.

49
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:24,425
Samgyupsal.

50
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:25,760
Because, you know,

51
00:06:26,803 --> 00:06:28,054
we deserve it.

52
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:30,598
Of course.

53
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:34,602
But you know,

54
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:37,480
you guys go ahead.

55
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:41,192
- Why?
- Nothing. We're not complete.

56
00:06:41,275 --> 00:06:42,443
Look.

57
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:45,238
General Norberto isn't here
because he's on vacation leave.

58
00:06:45,321 --> 00:06:46,989
And Alex is in Hong Kong.

59
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:48,282
Well,

60
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:51,494
it would've been more fun
if we were all here.

61
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,831
- Exactly.
- How about this?

62
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:57,375
Guys, let's just get burgers.

63
00:06:58,584 --> 00:07:00,419
- The buy-one-take-one deal!
- The buy-one-take-one deal!

64
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:03,172
- Let's go.
- Sure, sure, sure.

65
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:04,715
- Let's go.
- What do you mean, let's go?

66
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:05,800
We're getting burgers.

67
00:07:07,218 --> 00:07:08,177
Hey, wait.

68
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:11,806
It's Alex. Dara, come on, come on.

69
00:07:11,889 --> 00:07:13,141
Monitor the call.

70
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:14,308
- Okay.
- Let's head downstairs.

71
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:16,853
- Let's just wait.
- Okay, let's wait downstairs.

72
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,440
Good thing you finally called.

73
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:22,316
We've been waiting for your updates.

74
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:24,902
So much has happened.
There's been a lot going on, Bok.

75
00:07:25,486 --> 00:07:26,904
Okay, okay. But how are things?

76
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:28,614
Did you catch Chiara and Mikoy?

77
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,577
- Yes, they're with me now.
- <i>Nice!</i>

78
00:07:34,579 --> 00:07:35,830
How are they?

79
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:38,666
Did La Fornarina attack you or something?

80
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:41,169
I'm fine.

81
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:43,379
I eventually cornered them.

82
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:52,054
More than nice.
I'm so incredibly proud of you, Bok.

83
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:52,972
<i>You know that?</i>

84
00:07:53,055 --> 00:07:55,641
Because all the hard work
you've put in from the very beginning,

85
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:58,060
it's all paying off now with this case.

86
00:07:59,061 --> 00:07:59,896
Thank you.

87
00:08:00,396 --> 00:08:02,356
But we still have a long way to go.

88
00:08:03,691 --> 00:08:05,526
Of course, but…

89
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:07,028
don't think about that for now.

90
00:08:07,111 --> 00:08:09,822
<i>Okay? How about you?</i>

91
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:11,741
How are you over there?

92
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,035
Are you eating three meals
a day over there?

93
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:16,287
Are you drinking two liters of water?

94
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:18,581
And your steps,
are you still hitting 10,000 a day?

95
00:08:18,664 --> 00:08:20,666
Also, isn't it hot in Hong Kong?

96
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,585
The heat index is brutal
here in the Philippines.

97
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:24,128
- Hey!
- What?

98
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:25,379
Focus!

99
00:08:28,549 --> 00:08:30,593
Bok, can we save
the catching up for later?

100
00:08:31,802 --> 00:08:33,262
Of course, of course, Bok.

101
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:36,682
Sorry, we just can't help worrying.

102
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:37,767
We're worried about you here.

103
00:08:39,393 --> 00:08:41,646
<i>I understand. Thanks for your concern.</i>

104
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:43,231
I'm okay.

105
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:12,635
Mario. I'll head out first,
I still have to do my rounds.

106
00:09:13,135 --> 00:09:14,637
- Thank you very much, Chief!
- Okay.

107
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,055
I'll take care of the gate.

108
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:41,330
I guess you're worried
about Mikoy, aren't you?

109
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:43,708
Of course.

110
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:47,169
I don't even know how he's doing.

111
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:49,463
I do.

112
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:53,384
You do?

113
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:56,178
Of course I know something.

114
00:09:56,262 --> 00:10:00,850
You know, even confidential information
finds its way to me.

115
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:02,310
You know,

116
00:10:02,393 --> 00:10:06,647
the perks of having a father who's
the director general of the agency.

117
00:10:07,523 --> 00:10:10,234
And you're going to share
this information with me?

118
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:13,029
Of course.

119
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:16,824
I can feel your concern.

120
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:20,202
As a matter of fact, here's the latest.

121
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:23,372
The agency's best agent,
Special Agent Alex,

122
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:25,875
has already flown to Hong Kong.

123
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:31,839
And she's already figured out where Mikoy
and Chiara Valtrovi are.

124
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:35,176
So you think

125
00:10:36,677 --> 00:10:40,306
Agent Alex will find Mikoy?

126
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:45,102
Knowing Alex, it seems very possible.

127
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:49,565
I wouldn't be surprised
if right at this moment,

128
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:51,233
she's already caught both of them.

129
00:10:53,569 --> 00:10:55,196
I hope Mikoy is safe.

130
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:57,823
I hope so too.

131
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:17,259
What is this Lazarus Initiative?

132
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:24,016
Do you really want to know
about Project Lazarus?

133
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,518
Of course!

134
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:27,937
Okay, fine.

135
00:11:29,313 --> 00:11:30,689
What's the password?

136
00:11:33,901 --> 00:11:34,735
Tori-tori?

137
00:11:37,321 --> 00:11:38,656
Chuva-chuva?

138
00:11:43,744 --> 00:11:44,829
Locco-locco.

139
00:11:44,912 --> 00:11:46,997
Locco-locco!

140
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:48,207
You silly goose.

141
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:51,877
But on a serious note.

142
00:11:54,255 --> 00:11:56,215
Here's what Project Lazarus is.

143
00:11:56,298 --> 00:11:58,259
It's a mechanism of the state.

144
00:11:58,342 --> 00:12:00,970
It is only activated

145
00:12:01,053 --> 00:12:04,890
when all criminals need to be granted
legal protection

146
00:12:04,974 --> 00:12:07,601
to help fight all forms
of organized crime.

147
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:11,272
I don't remember that being
in the employee orientation manual.

148
00:12:11,355 --> 00:12:13,232
That's because it's top secret.

149
00:12:13,816 --> 00:12:15,818
So Project Lazarus

150
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:18,779
justifies the criminal acts

151
00:12:18,863 --> 00:12:21,157
of the people we're chasing? What?

152
00:12:23,576 --> 00:12:24,618
About this case.

153
00:12:24,702 --> 00:12:27,371
All these organized groups
around the world

154
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:30,166
are incredibly complex, deeply rooted,

155
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:32,251
and have vast networks,

156
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:33,878
including their connections.

157
00:12:41,218 --> 00:12:43,345
Like hitting the jackpot.

158
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:47,808
But if we ever manage to land a big fish,

159
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:50,978
we don't want to let
that opportunity slip away.

160
00:12:51,061 --> 00:12:53,856
Especially if they already know things

161
00:12:53,939 --> 00:12:57,151
that no matter how much
undercover work we do,

162
00:12:57,234 --> 00:12:58,861
we would never discover.

163
00:12:58,944 --> 00:13:00,029
Exactly.

164
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:18,547
I'm exercising.

165
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:20,382
I'm almost at 10,000 steps.

166
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:22,343
And it's part of my training too.

167
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:26,472
Is it because you're
running again in 2028?

168
00:13:26,555 --> 00:13:29,225
Or are you running for a higher office?

169
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:35,189
No, I don't have any plans. Not yet.

170
00:13:35,272 --> 00:13:39,193
I'm just training in case
I get thrown into something.

171
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,655
Wait a second. Why are you here?

172
00:13:42,738 --> 00:13:44,490
Is it an urgent matter?

173
00:13:46,408 --> 00:13:49,036
G.A.G.O. has called an emergency meeting.

174
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:51,747
About what?

175
00:13:52,331 --> 00:13:54,250
For the case of the Moravianos.

176
00:14:54,184 --> 00:14:58,147
Judge, meet our good-hearted lover boy,

177
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:00,482
Mikoy D. Pinagpala.

178
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:05,613
His heart is so big
for the people he loves

179
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:08,991
that it seems like everyone
he loves fits inside it.

180
00:15:09,783 --> 00:15:13,537
His family, his neighbors, his friends,

181
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:16,040
and his sweetheart.

182
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:20,586
Now that we've met our main character,

183
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:23,047
let's proceed with the story.

184
00:15:25,132 --> 00:15:28,427
<i>To put his youngest sibling</i>
<i>through school in Manila,</i>

185
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:34,475
Mikoy didn't hesitate
to try his luck abroad as an OFW.

186
00:15:34,558 --> 00:15:37,144
<i>But when he arrived in Prague,</i>

187
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:40,773
<i>it wasn't just a great opportunity</i>
<i>waiting for him.</i>

188
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:44,985
There was also a very beautiful woman.

189
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:47,529
It’s Chiara Valtrovi.

190
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:50,866
Half Filipino, half Czech.

191
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,160
Things happened very quickly.

192
00:15:53,243 --> 00:15:55,454
<i>They walked all over Prague.</i>

193
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:57,623
<i>They spent time together and had drinks.</i>

194
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:01,502
And they got a little romantic.

195
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:04,296
Got a little romantic?

196
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:07,383
They kissed, Judge. You know.

197
00:16:07,466 --> 00:16:08,592
They kissed already?

198
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:09,760
Of course.

199
00:16:09,843 --> 00:16:11,345
This is a modern love story.

200
00:16:11,428 --> 00:16:14,515
And like so many love stories,

201
00:16:14,598 --> 00:16:17,893
no one would follow it
or look forward to it

202
00:16:19,019 --> 00:16:20,354
without conflict,

203
00:16:20,437 --> 00:16:23,232
because it turns out this beautiful woman

204
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:26,193
is the only child

205
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,279
of Viktor Valtrovi.

206
00:16:29,363 --> 00:16:32,324
He is the leader of a European mafia

207
00:16:32,408 --> 00:16:35,327
known as the Moravianos.

208
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:41,250
<i>We've been monitoring</i>
<i>the Moravianos for quite some time.</i>

209
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:44,003
We only recently made a breakthrough.

210
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:48,298
When we turned Mikoy into an asset.

211
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:50,843
You convinced Mikoy to become an asset?

212
00:16:50,926 --> 00:16:54,304
I must say, your powers
of persuasion are impressive.

213
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:58,017
Well, it was more like
the power of desperation.

214
00:16:59,518 --> 00:17:03,272
<i>I'm sorry. I'm very desperate,</i>
<i>Mr. Pinagpala.</i>

215
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:04,398
<i>Was what we did right?</i>

216
00:17:05,399 --> 00:17:06,442
<i>But if we did nothing,</i>

217
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:08,360
more innocent people would suffer

218
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:11,822
because of the crimes committed
by the Moravianos and Viktor.

219
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:13,699
<i>Mikoy is just a simple man.</i>

220
00:17:14,324 --> 00:17:18,829
When it comes to doing what's right
for the greater good,

221
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:20,122
that's where he stands.

222
00:17:22,082 --> 00:17:27,171
<i>And he's willing to do anything</i>
<i>for the well-being of the people he loves.</i>

223
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:31,175
And in fact, Judge,
Mikoy took a bullet for Chiara.

224
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:35,345
This happened during a major event
hosted by the Valtrovis.

225
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:37,306
Move!

226
00:17:39,308 --> 00:17:42,478
<i>They were attacked and disrupted</i>
<i>by a local syndicate,</i>

227
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:44,438
<i>the Sinigang Cartel.</i>

228
00:17:46,273 --> 00:17:49,902
And we believe that was when their love
for each other deepened.

229
00:17:49,985 --> 00:17:53,447
And if you think their love story
is already complicated,

230
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:55,616
wait, there's more.

231
00:17:55,699 --> 00:17:58,202
Because Chiara Valtrovi

232
00:17:58,285 --> 00:18:01,830
isn't just a rich, spoiled nepo baby.

233
00:18:02,539 --> 00:18:06,543
She herself is the most powerful
of all the Moravianos.

234
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:16,053
<i>Yes, that's correct.</i>

235
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:21,517
<i>She earned that title</i>

236
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:24,645
<i>because of her extraordinary talent</i>
<i>in everything she does.</i>

237
00:18:44,706 --> 00:18:45,749
See?

238
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:47,626
Even you got shocked, Judge.

239
00:18:47,709 --> 00:18:50,254
That was exactly my reaction at first.

240
00:18:50,337 --> 00:18:53,173
When the lovebirds finally
learned each other's secrets,

241
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:54,091
here's what happened.

242
00:18:54,174 --> 00:18:56,635
The whites got mixed with the coloreds.

243
00:18:57,177 --> 00:18:59,972
<i>A major confrontation, a major chase,</i>

244
00:19:00,055 --> 00:19:01,598
<i>and a major shootout.</i>

245
00:19:02,182 --> 00:19:05,310
Just like that scene
from Mr. and Mrs. Smith.

246
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:19,533
After all the shooting and fighting,

247
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,410
<i>in the end,</i>

248
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:24,329
<i>they couldn't bring themselves</i>
<i>to kill each other.</i>

249
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:28,208
Because they had truly fallen in love.

250
00:19:29,084 --> 00:19:30,127
Right?

251
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:36,425
And this is the point
where our asset, Mikoy, defected.

252
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:37,509
Mikoy.

253
00:19:45,642 --> 00:19:49,021
Those two really have quite
the far-fetched love story.

254
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:56,236
And Special Agent Alex,

255
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:59,323
our best and brightest agent,

256
00:19:59,948 --> 00:20:01,450
tracked them down in Hong Kong

257
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:07,539
and successfully captured
the lovebirds in their cage.

258
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:18,175
Your petition has already
been submitted to the court.

259
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:22,387
The higher-ups will decide
whether or not to grant you immunity.

260
00:20:23,055 --> 00:20:24,640
Thank you very much, Alex.

261
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:27,226
We owe you our lives.

262
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:29,061
Thank you so much.

263
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:38,779
And because the two of them believe that
anything is possible through love,

264
00:20:38,862 --> 00:20:41,323
they are asking for immunity.

265
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:44,868
Immunity in exchange
for something valuable,

266
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:47,246
a very significant piece of information.

267
00:20:58,715 --> 00:21:03,387
According to them, this is the formidable
enemy we should prepare for

268
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:08,433
because Concordat's plan
is to invade the Philippines.

269
00:21:12,729 --> 00:21:13,897
But no,

270
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:17,234
because this Concordat

271
00:21:17,317 --> 00:21:21,446
is more than capable of destroying
everything we have.

272
00:21:21,530 --> 00:21:25,701
They could send us back
to the colonial era.

273
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:31,331
Appealing to your office

274
00:21:31,415 --> 00:21:35,252
to grant immunity to Mikoy and Chiara.

275
00:21:41,174 --> 00:21:44,970
What happens if our petition is denied?

276
00:21:45,053 --> 00:21:46,471
What will happen to us?

277
00:21:47,889 --> 00:21:49,766
Well, I'll just do what I have to do.

278
00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:53,228
I'll arrest both of you
and bring you back to the Philippines.

279
00:21:55,689 --> 00:21:57,065
What about Mom and Dad?

280
00:21:58,442 --> 00:22:01,194
If your immunity petition is denied,

281
00:22:01,278 --> 00:22:04,364
it will be much harder to protect
your parents, Chiara.

282
00:22:06,116 --> 00:22:08,493
But if we are granted immunity,

283
00:22:08,577 --> 00:22:12,080
can't we also petition the court
for Uncle Viktor and Aunt Donabel as well?

284
00:22:13,457 --> 00:22:17,544
We can try, but let's cross that bridge
when we get there.

285
00:22:20,047 --> 00:22:22,132
Let's focus first
on what happens to you two.

286
00:22:31,391 --> 00:22:34,352
After that long presentation,

287
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:39,524
you're asking me to protect
this couple, Chiara and Mikoy?

288
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:44,196
There are so many urgent matters
in this country.

289
00:23:23,777 --> 00:23:25,529
What? Got any news?

290
00:23:26,154 --> 00:23:27,030
Still nothing.

291
00:23:30,617 --> 00:23:32,160
It depends.

292
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:33,662
It's on a case-by-case basis.

293
00:23:39,584 --> 00:23:40,669
Didn't I tell you?

294
00:23:40,752 --> 00:23:42,671
Anything is possible!

295
00:23:43,296 --> 00:23:46,800
All right, Mr. Everything Is Possible.

296
00:23:54,516 --> 00:23:55,517
Sorry.

297
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:58,311
Alex! What are you doing?

298
00:23:58,395 --> 00:23:59,354
Hey!

299
00:23:59,437 --> 00:24:02,732
Chiara!

300
00:24:02,816 --> 00:24:04,276
Alex, what are you doing?

301
00:24:04,359 --> 00:24:06,695
- I'm sorry, Mikoy. I have no choice.
- Chiara, wake up!

302
00:24:06,778 --> 00:24:08,196
I have to turn you in.

303
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:09,656
What?

304
00:24:10,282 --> 00:24:12,659
Chiara! Chiara, wake up! Chiara!

305
00:24:13,785 --> 00:24:14,703
Oh…

306
00:24:56,328 --> 00:25:00,040
Are you even used to working in the heat?

307
00:25:00,123 --> 00:25:01,750
I'm telling you, you won't get any rest.

308
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:03,752
- You won't even have time to sit down.
- True.

309
00:25:05,670 --> 00:25:08,006
I'm not trying
to discourage you, okay, Sofie?

310
00:25:08,089 --> 00:25:10,342
But are you really sure
this is what you want?

311
00:25:30,403 --> 00:25:31,571
Hello!

312
00:25:32,864 --> 00:25:34,699
Hey, have mercy on me!

313
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,785
Let me out of here!

314
00:25:38,536 --> 00:25:39,663
Mom!
